Perfect — making branches in Git is super important for team projects! Here’s the step-by-step guide for your Herd Laravel project:

1️⃣ Start in your project root

Open your terminal (VS Code or Git Bash) inside your project folder:

cd C:/Users/gaura/Herd/boardgames.com

Check you’re on the main branch:

git status

You should see:

On branch main
nothing to commit, working tree clean
2️⃣ Pull latest changes from main

Always make sure your local main is up-to-date:

git pull origin main

This prevents conflicts when creating a new branch.

3️⃣ Create a new branch

Decide a name that reflects the work you’ll do. Example: adding authentication:

git checkout -b feature/authentication

feature/ is a common convention for new features

bugfix/ is often used for fixing bugs

This command creates and switches to the new branch immediately

Check your branch:

git branch

The * shows the current branch

Example output:

  main
* feature/authentication
4️⃣ Work on your branch

Make changes in VS Code

Stage and commit your changes:

git add .
git commit -m "Add login and registration pages"
5️⃣ Push the branch to GitHub
git push -u origin feature/authentication

The -u sets the branch to track the remote branch

Now your branch appears on GitHub

6️⃣ Create a Pull Request (PR)

Go to your repo on GitHub

GitHub usually shows: “Your recently pushed branch” → click Compare & Pull Request

Fill in a title and description → assign reviewers if needed

Merge into main after approval

7️⃣ Switch back to main

After your branch is merged:

git checkout main
git pull origin main

Now your main is up-to-date

You can start the next branch for a new feature
